## üöÄ Quick Start Guide

### Step 1: Reload VS Code

```bash
# Reload window to pick up new MCP configuration
# Cmd+Shift+P ‚Üí "Developer: Reload Window"
```

### Step 2: Configure Gemini (Recommended)

1. Get API key: https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
2. Open Roo Code settings
3. Select "Gemini" provider
4. Enter your API key
5. Select model: `gemini-3-pro-preview`

### Step 3: Enable MCP Servers

1. Open Roo Code settings
2. Go to "MCP" tab
3. You should see 17 servers listed
4. Toggle ON the servers you want to use
5. Configure any required secrets (API keys)

### Step 4: Install Browser Extension (Optional)

1. Chrome ‚Üí `chrome://extensions/`
2. Enable "Developer mode"
3. Load unpacked ‚Üí `/Users/imorgado/Projects/Roo-Code/browser-extension/`

### Step 5: Test Everything

```
# In Roo Code chat:
"List all available MCP tools"
"Take a screenshot of the current browser tab"
"Use Docker to list running containers"
"Search GitHub for Claude repositories"
```

